<subSubSection id="C3076564FFA5FF92FF23DB3FE1B8EEF9" pageId="7" pageNumber="94" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA236EFFFA5FF92FF23DB3FE35EEE83" blockId="7.[189,311,1385,1411]" box="[189,311,1385,1411]" pageId="7" pageNumber="94">
<heading id="D0EA8183FFA5FF92FF23DB3FE35EEE83" bold="true" box="[189,311,1385,1411]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="94" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B969EAFDFFA5FF92FF23DB3FE35EEE83" bold="true" box="[189,311,1385,1411]" pageId="7" pageNumber="94">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA236EFFFA5FF92FF23DBCEE1B8EEF9" blockId="7.[188,1400,1432,1529]" pageId="7" pageNumber="94">
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1D4D6CFFA5FF92FEAFDBCFE05BEEB2" authority="Sánchez-Ruiz &amp; Martínez &amp; Bonaldo, 2022" authorityName="Sánchez-Ruiz &amp; Martínez &amp; Bonaldo" authorityYear="2022" box="[305,562,1432,1459]" class="Arachnida" family="Caponiidae" genus="Caponina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bochalema" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B969EAFDFFA5FF92FEAFDBCFE05BEEB2" box="[305,562,1432,1459]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="94">Caponina bochalema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25A5786FFA5FF92FDA7DBCFE0FCEEB3" box="[569,661,1433,1459]" pageId="7" pageNumber="94" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be easily distinguished from other Colombian species by having a small, acuminated cymbium, a large and oval tegulum (size greater than cymbium length), and an embolus with a short and needle-shaped tip (
<figureCitation id="13262A6AFFA5FF92FD75DB89E107EEF9" box="[747,878,1503,1529]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[191,234,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-15@8.[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. A–B, E–G. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. E. Left palp, retrolateral view. F. Left palp, ventral view. G. Left palp, prolateral view. – C–D, H–J. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. Habitus, ventral view. H. Left palp, retrolateral view. I. Left palp, ventral view. J. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A–D = 1.5 mm; E–J = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468230/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="94">Figs 3E–G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13262A6AFFA5FF92FCE4DB89E1ACEEF9" box="[890,965,1503,1529]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1319,768,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-165@9.[189,1398,761,1857]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. A–C. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). A. Left palp, retrolateral view. B. Left palp, ventral view. C. Left palp, prolateral view. – D–F. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). D. Left palp, retrolateral view. E. Left palp, ventral view. F. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars = 1 mm. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468234" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468234/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="94">4A–C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
