<paragraph id="8BA236EFFFABFF9CFF23DF5FE14BEA69" blockId="9.[189,1399,265,362]" pageId="9" pageNumber="96">
COLORATION. Carapace pale orange (
<figureCitation id="13262A6AFFABFF9CFDF2DF5FE0B9EA23" box="[620,720,265,291]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[191,234,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-15@8.[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. A–B, E–G. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. E. Left palp, retrolateral view. F. Left palp, ventral view. G. Left palp, prolateral view. – C–D, H–J. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. Habitus, ventral view. H. Left palp, retrolateral view. I. Left palp, ventral view. J. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A–D = 1.5 mm; E–J = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468230/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="96">Figs 3A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13262A6AFFABFF9CFD41DF5FE16AEA24" box="[735,771,265,292]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,396,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-15@10.[187,1396,396,1853]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 5. A–B. Caponina alejandroi sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3747). A. Prosoma, dorsal view. B. Prosoma, ventral view. –C–D. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). C. Prosoma, dorsal view. D. Prosoma, ventral view. – E–F. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). E. Prosoma, dorsal view. F. Prosoma, ventral view. Scale bars = 1.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468236/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="96">5E</figureCitation>
). Chelicerae, endites, labium, sternum and legs pale orange (
<figureCitation id="13262A6AFFABFF9CFEBFDF7AE3EFEA46" box="[289,390,300,326]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[191,234,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-15@8.[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. A–B, E–G. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. E. Left palp, retrolateral view. F. Left palp, ventral view. G. Left palp, prolateral view. – C–D, H–J. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. Habitus, ventral view. H. Left palp, retrolateral view. I. Left palp, ventral view. J. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A–D = 1.5 mm; E–J = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468230/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="96">Figs 3B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13262A6AFFABFF9CFE09DF7AE3D3EA47" box="[407,442,300,327]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,396,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-15@10.[187,1396,396,1853]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 5. A–B. Caponina alejandroi sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3747). A. Prosoma, dorsal view. B. Prosoma, ventral view. –C–D. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). C. Prosoma, dorsal view. D. Prosoma, ventral view. – E–F. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). E. Prosoma, dorsal view. F. Prosoma, ventral view. Scale bars = 1.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468236/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="96">5F</figureCitation>
). Abdomen pale beige (
<figureCitation id="13262A6AFFABFF9CFD7CDF7AE101EA46" box="[738,872,300,326]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[191,234,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-15@8.[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. A–B, E–G. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. E. Left palp, retrolateral view. F. Left palp, ventral view. G. Left palp, prolateral view. – C–D, H–J. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. Habitus, ventral view. H. Left palp, retrolateral view. I. Left palp, ventral view. J. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A–D = 1.5 mm; E–J = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468230/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="96">Fig. 3A–B</figureCitation>
), covered by many brown and short setae, epigastric region pale orange. Spinnerets pale beige.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA236EFFFABFF9CFF23DFC7E1A6EACE" blockId="9.[189,1398,401,463]" pageId="9" pageNumber="96">MEASUREMENTS. Total length 3.18, carapace 1.25 long, 1.08 wide, 0.29 high, sternum 0.80 long, 0.71 wide, legs: I: 3.44; II: 3.29; III: 3.00; IV: 4.07, abdomen 2.15 long.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA236EFFFABFF9CFF23DFA0E288E9C0" blockId="9.[189,1399,501,704]" pageId="9" pageNumber="96">
MORPHOLOGY. Carapace flat with soft cuticle. Six eyes, AME largest, dark, separated by about half their diameter, ALE pale translucent and smaller than AME, PLE pale translucent and smaller than ALE. Palpal femur with dorsal tubercle and small prolateral stridulatory pick (
<figureCitation id="13262A6AFFABFF9CFB8CDC6AE607E956" box="[1042,1134,572,598]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[191,234,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-15@8.[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. A–B, E–G. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. E. Left palp, retrolateral view. F. Left palp, ventral view. G. Left palp, prolateral view. – C–D, H–J. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. Habitus, ventral view. H. Left palp, retrolateral view. I. Left palp, ventral view. J. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A–D = 1.5 mm; E–J = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468230/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="96">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
); cymbium very small and pointed, tegulum very large and oval, with long and thin embolus directed anteriorly protruding ventrally from approximately middle surface of tegulum, embolus tip short and sharp (
<figureCitation id="13262A6AFFABFF9CFB2BDCD4E751E99C" box="[1205,1336,642,668]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[191,234,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-15@8.[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. A–B, E–G. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. E. Left palp, retrolateral view. F. Left palp, ventral view. G. Left palp, prolateral view. – C–D, H–J. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. Habitus, ventral view. H. Left palp, retrolateral view. I. Left palp, ventral view. J. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A–D = 1.5 mm; E–J = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468230/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="96">Figs 3E–G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13262A6AFFABFF9CFADADCD4E2BDE9C0" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1319,768,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-165@9.[189,1398,761,1857]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. A–C. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). A. Left palp, retrolateral view. B. Left palp, ventral view. C. Left palp, prolateral view. – D–F. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). D. Left palp, retrolateral view. E. Left palp, ventral view. F. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars = 1 mm. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468234" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468234/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="96">4A– C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
